HEADWORD: Parataxis
<hw>Par`a*tax"is</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<?/ a placing beside, fr. <?/ to place beside.]</ety> <fld>(Gram.)</fld>
<def>The mere ranging of propositions one after another, without
indicating their connection or interdependence; -- opposed to
<contr>syntax</contr>.</def> <rj><au>Brande & C.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

